This paper deals with security issues in Mobile Ad Hoc Networks (MANET), which is a subfield of computer networking (cs.NI). The paper specifically focuses on Denial of Service (DoS) attacks, which is a subfield of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed solution is a distributed algorithm, which involves coordination among multiple nodes, making it relevant to distributed computing (cs.DC). The algorithm involves identifying misbehaving nodes, which is a problem in data mining and machine learning (cs.DS). Finally, the algorithm aims to improve the overall system performance, which is a goal of systems and control theory (cs.SY).
